  <discussion>Plants identified as Syntrichia cainii from elsewhere in North America (e.g.,
        Kansas, Colorado, and California) are probably incorrectly identified. The difficulty comes
        from several other species (especially S. norvegica) having scattered neotenic races in
        which the mature leaves lack awns and thus appear superficially similar to S. cainii. More
